oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Mr. Thompson and Mr. Carter
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of Franklin Blevins Thompson (1847-1903) and Mr. Carter next to a horse-drawn buggy on Williams Island. The horse in this photo was named "Dan." In February 1977, a fire on Williams Island destroyed over 100 acres and some structures including a barn.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Men; Horses; Carts & wagons
